3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"GMX calculates funding rates hourly using a combination of price premium/discount and interest rate differentials between long and short positions. The platform's oracle-based pricing eliminates funding rate manipulation common on order book exchanges. When SUI's spot price diverges from the perpetual mark price, the funding mechanism automatically adjusts to incentivize convergence. Funding payments are settled directly from the GLP pool, ensuring consistent execution regardless of counterparty availability."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SUI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI represents one of the most actively traded Layer 1 tokens with significant funding rate volatility due to ecosystem developments and validator staking dynamics. The token's correlation with broader Layer 1 trends creates predictable funding patterns during market cycles. GMX's oracle-based pricing provides more stable funding calculations compared to order book exchanges prone to manipulation in mid-cap altcoin pairs."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI/USDT funding rates on GMX typically range from -0.5% to +2% annually, with pronounced spikes during major ecosystem announcements and DeFi integrations. Layer 1 tokens like SUI exhibit higher funding volatility than established assets due to staking yield fluctuations and ecosystem growth phases. Historical data shows funding rates tend to peak during Sui network upgrades and major validator onboarding periods. The hourly settlement frequency on GMX allows for more granular capture of these rate movements compared to 8-hour settlement cycles on centralized exchanges."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between GMX and major CEXs like Binance or OKX frequently yields 5-15% APR opportunities when SUI funding rates diverge. GMX's oracle-based pricing often lags high-volume CEX price movements by 1-3 minutes, creating temporary arbitrage windows for sophisticated traders. The platform's 0.05%-0.07% trading fees are competitive for funding rate arbitrage strategies, especially when rates exceed 0.1% daily. Automated strategies work particularly well due to GMX's consistent oracle updates and predictable settlement timing."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Oracle dependency represents the primary risk factor for GMX perpetuals, with Chainlink price feeds occasionally experiencing delays during high volatility periods. Position sizes should account for GMX's price impact mechanics, as large trades can experience slippage against the GLP pool. SUI's mid-tier market cap makes it susceptible to sudden liquidity drains during market stress, potentially affecting funding rate calculations. Traders should monitor GLP pool utilization rates, as high utilization can impact position opening/closing during volatile periods, affecting arbitrage execution timing."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often do SUI/USDT funding rates update on GMX?","answer":"GMX calculates and applies funding rates every hour for all perpetual pairs including SUI/USDT. This frequent settlement allows traders to capture smaller rate movements compared to traditional 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What makes GMX's SUI funding rates different from CEX rates?","answer":"GMX uses oracle-based pricing rather than order book dynamics, leading to more stable funding calculations. The rates are less susceptible to manipulation but may lag during rapid price movements due to oracle update frequency."},{"question":"Can I earn funding fees without directional exposure on SUI?","answer":"Yes, by taking opposite positions on GMX and a CEX simultaneously, you can collect funding rate differentials while maintaining delta-neutral exposure. This strategy works particularly well during high funding rate periods on Layer 1 tokens."},{"question":"What position limits exist for SUI perpetuals on GMX?","answer":"Position limits depend on GLP pool capacity and current utilization. SUI typically supports positions up to several hundred thousand dollars, but large positions may experience price impact due to the AMM-style liquidity provision model."}]}]
